This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and sentiment analysis. The paper proposes a new approach for aspect-level sentiment classification that takes into account the syntactic dependencies within sentences. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as these fields often intersect with natural language processing and sentiment analysis.
